I found a more realistic zero-upfront path than the current code: make the stolen token the `tokenOut`/fee token, route `transferFrom(victim, Dexible, amount)`, and let Dexible pay its own fees out of the stolen output before sending the remainder to the verifier. That preserves the original exploit path and avoids needing attacker-funded fee inventory when a victim allowance exists.
